    "body":  "Codex review: APPROVED\n\nI reviewed #307 at `fe94cad`.\n\nChecks:\n- Scope is exactly the two intended files: `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/tests.rs` and `crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs`; `+111/-0`, no Cargo/edge changes, `git diff --check` clean.\n- The new `reset_camera_frames_cad_projection_scene` test is load-bearing for the CAD-projection arm: it constructs a CAD shell with empty prebuilt meshes and populated `cad_entity` / `projection` / `cad_world`, uses a non-unit 4x2x6 cuboid whose framing differs from the default fallback, clobbers both `eye` and `target`, and asserts `reset_camera()` reproduces the CAD projection framing.\n- The crate-root `MENU-BAR ARC` doc entry fills the omission without stale/private rustdoc links: private `menu::...` items are plain code spans, while public handoff links remain valid.\n- Near-cap files remain untouched as intended.\n- CI is fully green: 13/13, `MERGEABLE/CLEAN`.\n\nContent approved. Merge still requires explicit human authorization.\r\n",
